    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required thresholds at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package based on the primary hemolysis QoI showing Monte Carlo-quantified uncertainty within regulatory tolerance at three of five operating points, and the overall risk posture being managed through additional clinical monitoring commitments. Aleatory variability in wall shear stress was noted qualitatively but no structured UQ link was established for that validation result, representing a residual gap acknowledged by the team.",
